To install:

- Temurin JDK (Java 25): Download the Linux x64 (or AArch64 for Mac/ARM) .tar.gz from Adoptium Releases.
- Scala CLI: Download the Linux binary (e.g., scala-cli-x86_64-pc-linux.gz) from the Scala CLI GitHub Releases.
  - Action: Decompress it, rename it to scala-cli, move it into a bin/ folder in your project, and make it executable: chmod +x bin/scala-cli.

- Run launch.sh to install in local env [
#!/bin/bash

# Get the absolute path of the directory where this script is located
BASE_DIR="$(cd "$(dirname "${BASH_SOURCE[0]}")" &> /dev/null && pwd)"

# Set the path to your specific JVM folder
export JAVA_HOME="$BASE_DIR/jvm/jdk-25.0.1+8"

# Add local bin and local java to the temporary PATH
export PATH="$BASE_DIR/bin:$JAVA_HOME/bin:$PATH"

echo "---------------------------------------"
echo "Scala Portable Environment Loaded (Linux)!"
echo "---------------------------------------"
echo "Java Home: $JAVA_HOME"
echo ""

# Verify Java is found
java -version
echo ""

# Verify Scala-CLI is found
scala-cli --version
echo "---------------------------------------"

# Start a new sub-shell to keep the environment active (equivalent to cmd /k)
exec $SHELL

], making sure to make it executable : chmod +x launch.sh

- To build: scala-cli --power package projects/web_app/app.sc --assembly -o app.jar --force
- To run: java -jar app.jar --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8080
